/*
    True comptime — Route A dispatch on builtin.os.

    `comptime switch (builtin.os)` folds at compile time; only the
    winning arm is type-checked. The non-host arm is dead code and is
    not exhaustiveness-checked (the elimination is the point).

    Host-independent: both arms produce i32, so the function types the
    same regardless of which arm wins (we just can't observe WHICH
    arm without running the binary; a separate test forces an
    overflow on the dead arm to prove dead-branch elimination).
*/

builtin :: @import("builtin")

main :: pub fn() i32
    comptime switch (builtin.os)
        .macos => 1
        .linux => 2
